OL,8,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,9,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,11,FKhalusha's lawyer, John Maina Ndegwa,
OL,12,Ftold journalists his client was
OL,13,Ftortured and forced to confess and
OL,14,Fmaintained he was not guilty.
OL,16,FMr Ndegwa said he last spoke to
OL,17,FKhalusha on Friday when he was
OL,18,Fpresented in court. "I'm also
OL,19,Fconfounded by the news," he added.
